			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				there seems to be so much confusion surrounding this one item, I decided to post my .02 in hopes of clearing some of it up. I must apologize in advance if I mislead anyone or fail to post correctly any information, thus I invite you to create a character on The Rathe and join me so that we can figure it out.<BR>
<BR>
While in Hate last night the servers came down and needed to be re-popped meaning that Inny was up shortly after the re-pop. I looted the Encyclopedia off of Inny after a fierce battle that took almost half of our group.<BR>
<BR>
Upon casting a pet, I was still able to cast my 56 servant of bones and pull up a green pet. The pet was very very large in size as compared to a normal pet and I think that it will cast your normal pet, but the encyclopedia turns that normal pet into a pt 2 levels higher than it would be otherwise. Confused yet? I was able to cast 3 green pets with this in my hand. strange. Also, it is virtually impossible for me, with or without the encyclopedia, to cast a spectre pet at level 56 since I do not possess the spectre pet spell. You will still have a monk or a rogue, depending on which spell you cast. Hope this clears up any rumors....<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

